Required Payment Flow Normalization

Centralize this in one function.

Example:

export function normalizePOSPaymentFlow(input: unknown): POSPaymentFlow {
  if (input === "full_payment") return "full";
  if (input === "partial_payment_dp") return "dp";
  if (input === "full") return "full";
  if (input === "dp") return "dp";
  if (input === "multi") return "multi";
  if (input === "split") return "split";
  return "full";
}

Required mapping:

full_payment        -> full
partial_payment_dp  -> dp
full                -> full
dp                  -> dp
multi               -> multi
split               -> split
undefined           -> full unless partialAmount implies dp

Only shared layer should do this.

Do not repeat this mapping inside Retail or Restaurant hooks.

---

Required Fresh Cart Behavior

Fresh cart means the cashier is paying from a cart that does not yet have a saved "orderId".

Fresh Cart + Full Payment

Allowed behavior:

- may use create-and-pay if current implementation is safe;
- must create exactly one payment row;
- must set paid only after payment row covers total;
- must clear cart only after success;
- must not require orders_queue.

Fresh Cart + DP

Allowed behavior:

- may use create-and-pay only if it persists one down_payment row and leaves order partial;
- if create-and-pay cannot safely do that, use createOrder -> recordPayment;
- must create one down_payment row;
- must not mark order paid if DP amount < total;
- must show remaining amount.

Fresh Cart + Multi Payment

Required behavior:

- must create order first with createOrder;
- then call recordPayment once per payment line;
- max 2 payment lines in P9/P9.1;
- each payment row must use payment_flow=multi and payment_kind=multi_line;
- total of payment lines must cover remaining amount for paid status;
- must never send payment_flow=multi to create-and-pay.

Fresh Cart + Split Bill

Required behavior:

- must create order first with createOrder;
- then call recordPayment for paid split lines;
- max 4 split bills;
- each split payment row must use payment_flow=split and payment_kind=split_line;
- original order must not be paid until all splits are paid and total paid covers order total;
- must never send payment_flow=split to create-and-pay.

---

Required Saved / Active Order Behavior

Saved/active order means the payment has an existing "orderId".

Existing Order + Full Payment

- call recordPayment once;
- payment_flow=full;
- payment_kind=full_payment;
- amount should cover remaining amount.

Existing Order + DP

- call recordPayment once;
- payment_flow=dp;
- payment_kind=down_payment if amount is less than remaining;
- payment_kind=remaining_payment if amount completes remaining;
- keep status partial when amount does not cover total.

Existing Order + Multi Payment

- call recordPayment once per payment line;
- max 2 lines;
- payment_flow=multi;
- payment_kind=multi_line;
- do not call create-and-pay.

Existing Order + Split Bill

- call recordPayment once per paid split line;
- max 4 splits;
- payment_flow=split;
- payment_kind=split_line;
- do not call create-and-pay.

Split id handling:

- If splitId is a valid UUID, send it as split_id.
- If splitId is a UI/session-only id, do not send it as split_id.
- Store UI/session split id in metadata, for example metadata.session_split_id.

This avoids invalid UUID backend errors.

